OL,3,CExecutive accused of 'Polyfilla
OL,4,Cpolitics' over health pay
OL,6,F"This is 'Polyfilla politics' from the
OL,7,FExecutive, make-do and mend. These are
OL,8,Fpromises that have been made to health
OL,9,Fcare workers for years now, they
OL,10,Fshould have planned this in their
OL,11,Fbudgets."
OL,13,FHealth trade unions say they will hold
OL,14,F"detailed" talks with the health
OL,15,Fminister and officials on the next
OL,16,Fsteps to restore pay parity.
OL,18,FUnison has said it is concerned about
OL,19,Fhow the money has been found to pay
OL,20,Ftheir workers and crucially how it
OL,21,Fwill be paid for in the future.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G2/7
